text: Mach'ayniyuq (Quechua mach'ay cave, -ni, -yuq suffixes, "the one with a cave (or caves)", also spelled Machayniocc) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru high, about . It is situated in the Ayacucho Region, Cangallo Province, Paras District. Mach'ayniyuq lies southeast of Qarampa. ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Ayacucho Region
title: Mach'ayniyuq
